 Government officials in Louisiana, Mississippi and Texas yesterday advised or ordered more than 2m people to evacuate coastal areas.
 A hurricane warning was in effect yesterday along 470 miles of Gulf coast from Pascagoula, Mississippi, to Galvestone, Texas.
 The town of Homestead, near the centre of the storm, was largely flattened, including a local air force base.
 A spokesman for State Farm Insurance said he believed the company had roughly 20 per cent of the Florida market.
 The mutually-owned company has no reinsurance.
